review_title: A nice hotel in a peaceful part of the island
review_text_liked: The location of this hotel is beautiful with well-maintained gardens attracting many butterflies and birds, a great sea view from the restaurant area and well positioned to see some great sunsets. The villas are private and very comfortable. However, something you may want to consider when booking is accessibility to the en suite bathrooms and the outdoor shower. Some of the villas have a large step and narrow doors, if this may be a problem you should consider discussing it with the hotel. The restaurant is okay, but there are better options a ten to fifteen minutes‚Äô walk away. The breakfast too was okay, but perhaps not if you have a big appetite. The pool area was good and quite well maintained. A nice beach area too, although again some deep steps to reach it.
review_text_disliked: We knew from previous reviews that the service in the restaurant could be slow but was okay with this in the evening, although really did not expect it at breakfast. It is a good job we had nothing planned! May want to discuss with the hotel if a steep step and narrow doors may be a problem.

review_text_disliked: Wi-Fi only available in bungalows, not in public areas.... Guests must refill their water bottles in the dining room. There is only one refilling station. The accommodation is cheap but the food is expensive with large selection of western style foods and limited Balinese options - but it's good. Due to position of property you really need your own transport if you want to get something else..... The air conditioning in the room was good but when lying in bed the air flow is on my face. Tried redirecting airflow but the position is opposite bed. When trying to sleep, the air con is annoying so have to turn off. Then it gets hot during the night and have to turn back on. Then turn off again because the air flow is on my face/head.... The bed was 2 single beds pushed together so could not spread out in the bed. It was very uncomfortable in the middle

review_title: Nice resort to relax, far away from the mass tourism
review_text_liked: Very comfortable bed, outdoor shower, clean room with a balcony and a view over the beautiful garden. The swimming pool is big and clean (you can even swim in it). The food at the restaurant was good. There's a secret beach (but watch out for the wild sea here) and you can walk up to have a view over the ocean and amazing sunsets. It's a very nice place to relax and to be far away from the mass tourism in Bali.
review_text_disliked: The staff could have been better. We messaged them on WhatsApp to book an extra night and the only response we got was 'wait, I have to check'. Since we didn't get any response, we booked the extra night through Booking. You have to wait a long time to get your dinner at the restaurant (the food is good though).

room_view: Two Bedroom Villa with Garden View
review_text_liked: The property is charming, and the pool is great.
review_text_disliked: The property is very understaffed, so we were left feeling neglected - and our expectations are not very high. There is a feeling of Miss Haversham about the place. Leaving us imagining what it would have like in its hay day. Laundry was 4 times more expensive than anywhere else we stayed and we could only pay that in cash, even though Gajah Mina was on the invoice. We were also disappointed to discover our minimal breakfast options (paid for and included) was a lesser version than other villas. This made us feel like we were somehow less valued than other guests (we booked the last villa available) - so we went out for breakfast after the first day (lots of great options in Balian) and we left Balian a day early. We had to walk past the neighbour's dogs (to get to Balian town and beach) who had developed a 'pack' mentality and one even nipped my daughter! So take a stick/handbag when walking into town and don't ask to borrow the hotel's umbrella if it's chucking it down, as they are "only for use in reception"...

We had to walk past the neighbour's dogs (to get to Balian town and beach) who had developed a 'pack' mentality and one even nipped my daughter! So take a stick/handbag when walking into town and don't ask to borrow the hotel's umbrella if it's chucking it down, as they are "only for use in reception"...
en_full_review: title: Charming property but tired & understaffed. liked: The property is charming, and the pool is great. disliked: The property is very understaffed, so we were left feeling neglected - and our expectations are not very high. There is a feeling of Miss Haversham about the place. Leaving us imagining what it would have like in its hay day. Laundry was 4 times more expensive than anywhere else we stayed and we could only pay that in cash, even though Gajah Mina was on the invoice. We were also disappointed to discover our minimal breakfast options (paid for and included) was a lesser version than other villas. This made us feel like we were somehow less valued than other guests (we booked the last villa available) - so we went out for breakfast after the first day (lots of great options in Balian) and we left Balian a day early. We had to walk past the neighbour's dogs (to get to Balian town and beach) who had developed a 'pack' mentality and one even nipped my daughter! So take a stick/handbag when walking into town and don't ask to borrow the hotel's umbrella if it's chucking it down, as they are "only for use in reception"...

review_title: Rustic, quiet and simply amazing ! A couples paradise
review_text_liked: Well! Where do I start? We loved this place. It was a very quiet time of year, a bonus for us!! We have a villa that is close to the pool and the ocean view. This place is rustic, it's out of the way, and a hidden gem. It is value for money, quiet (apart from the ocean crashing on the cliffs at night and the beautiful sound of the birds and the insects). We stayed 7 nights. Now Balian is a very quiet place and there are a few different accomodations in the area, but not a great deal to choose from. We were there on our round Bali trip and I was looking for locations for my next retreat. It is a very quiet place. So if you are looking for busy, shopping, night life. Do not visit Balian. But those of you who love peace and quiet and want to get away from it all. Especially if you love surfing, then this little hideaway is for you. It definitely suits couples. We found some wonderful eating places in the area and there is a great restaurant on site, where you can have all your meals. They are rated for their food and the qualitiy. I highly recommend this place if you are looking to get away from it all and want a break that is nice and quiet. It is gorgeous and the swimming pool it amazing. There is a wondeful nature walk (really rustic) and it takes you down to a beach that you can walk for miles and see no one (it's all volcanic sand, so be prepared to get black feet lol). Anyways we love it and I will definitely be going back there again very soon. What a wonderful gem !! Thank you sooooo much !!

review_title: Resort with potential - if the management would care
review_text_liked: The resort is located on a scenic cliff area in a beautiful garden landscape, with lots of birds singing in the morning. The pool is long, nice and clean. The bungalows were nice and clean (apart from the occasional cockroach or other small wildlife) and the large double bed (made with two separate mattresses) was comfortable, hot shower and aircons were working well. The home-made bread for breakfast was nice. The staff was nice, as long as there were no issues to discuss/ resolve (see below). For the bungalows and the garden and cliff landscape with the small ‚Äòprivate‚Äô beach, I would give four to five stars, if the issues described below were not tarnishing the experience a bit.
review_text_disliked: We booked two bungalows through booking.com, and expected to pay the price agreed on there. We were then asked to pay an additional 2% credit card charge - something none of the other 15+ hotels we stayed during this trip charged. Next we were shown ‚Äòour‚Äô bungalows, described on booking.com as two room bungalows with a bedroom with a double bed, and a separate living room with a sofa bed. What we got were bungalows with only a single bedroom with one large bed (the 1.2 meter sofa in there can hardly be called a sofa bed). When we pointed out that we booked bungalows with a separate living room, we were simply told to contact booking.com if we have an issue with this booking‚Ä¶ It appears to us that it would certainly be the hotel‚Äôs responsibility to make sure that the description on the booking platform matches what they actually provide. The price we paid for the bungalows is not too high for the single room bungalows, but if you expect a two-room bungalow with a bed in each room as advertised, and the response you get from the hotel is a sloppy ‚Äútalk to booking.com if you are not happy‚Äù, than that is certainly not good. The drinking water provided in the room is chlorinated tap water. The choice for breakfast was very limited. Two slices of bread with butter and jam was the top choice. Check-out time is 11am. When we asked whether it would be possible to check out around 12, we were told that this is not possible. When we passed by those bungalows again at 1pm, both bungalows were still in the same state as when we left (the beds not made, rooms not cleaned, nobody there‚Ä¶). We saw one other guest in the resort the whole time we were there‚Ä¶

The drinking water provided in the room is chlorinated tap water. The choice for breakfast was very limited. Two slices of bread with butter and jam was the top choice. Check-out time is 11am. When we asked whether it would be possible to check out around 12, we were told that this is not possible. When we passed by those bungalows again at 1pm, both bungalows were still in the same state as when we left (the beds not made, rooms not cleaned, nobody there‚Ä¶). We saw one other guest in the resort the whole time we were there‚Ä¶.
